A '''tree swing cartoon '''or''' tire swing cartoon''' is a humorous graphical [[metaphor]] that purports to explain communication pitfalls in the [[division of labor]] in the development of a product.<ref name="Brechner2011">{{cite book|author=Eric Brechner|title=I. M. Wright's "Hard Code": A Decade of Hard-Won Lessons from Microsoft®|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MjvORrOl-AoC&pg=PT127|accessdate=19 July 2013|date=22 July 2011|publisher=O'Reilly Media, Inc.|isbn=978-0-7356-6488-3|pages=127–}}</ref><ref name="Inc2008">{{cite book|author=Ouellette & Associates Consulting, Inc|title=Leading IT Transformation: The Roadmap for Success|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kDpgXRBA_CcC&pg=PA61|accessdate=19 July 2013|date=3 October 2008|publisher=Kendall Hunt Publishing Co.|isbn=978-0-7575-5833-7|pages=61–}}</ref> It depicts how different departments implement or describe a [[tire swing]] attached to a tree, and how different it is from what the customer actually intended. It has also been used to illustrate the [[waterfall model]] of software development.<ref name="Smith-Atakan2006">{{cite book|author=Serengul Smith-Atakan|title=Human-Computer Interaction|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tjPHVhncBzYC&pg=PA52|accessdate=19 July 2013|year=2006|publisher=Cengage Learning EMEA|isbn=978-1-84480-454-2|pages=52–}}</ref>


The original version appears to be from the early 1970s, possibly 1973.<ref name="Clark2009">{{cite book|author=Cindy Dell Clark|title=Transactions at Play|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jcHOugXx33wC&pg=PA135|accessdate=19 July 2013|date=16 May 2009|publisher=University Press of America|isbn=978-0-7618-4486-0|pages=135–}}</ref><ref name=britannicablog>{{cite web|title=The Classic "Tree Swing" Example of Production and Customer Service Gone Awry|url=http://blogs.britannica.com/2009/10/the-classic-tree-swing-example-of-production-and-customer-service-gone-awry|work=Encyclopædia Britannica Blog|publisher=Encyclopædia Britannica|accessdate=19 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.is/FgxPK|title=Origins of the tree swing pictures|publisher=BusinessBalls.com|accessdate=2018-10-15}}</ref> Many variants of it appeared later in several books on education, software engineering and management.<ref>{{cite web|title=Origins of the tree swing pictures (new versions)|url=http://www.businessballs.com/treeswing.htm|publisher=BusinessBalls.com|accessdate=2013-07-19}}</ref>

